dismissalText.commentary: William Porterfield b Burl 49 (69b 7x4 0x6) SR: 71.01

dismissalComment.html: bowled him! Porterfield falls short of a fifty. Burl rewarded for his eight nicely landed legbreaks that built the pressure. Rips this in from a length outside off as Porterfield backs away to try and punch through cover. Past the inside edge and into middle and off
got him! Stirling won't become the second ODI batsman to get seven 50-plus scores in a row. Short of a length outside off, looks to cut but that gets big on him late and he can only edge it behind
taken at mid-on. Balbirnie is late on the sweep and manages only a top edge out to the fielder. Length at off stump, pushed flat and he wants to sweep but is in terrible shape to pull it off

commentTextItems.html: and that is 3-0! Length outside off, pushes at it on the front foot, gets a bat pad pitch side on the off side and KOB calls through for the run

commentPostTextItems.html: 6:11pm And that is all from our coverage! Thanks for joining us. Catch you for the T20Is.

Porterfield: We set out to win the series and obivously at 2-0 to win it 3-0, pretty good. Started back in May, quite a few cricketers have come in. It's really pleasing that the lads are coming in and making contributions. There's depth in that pool of players and the confidence is right up there.

Murtagh: I'm getting on a bit now but still enjoying my cricket. These boys keep me young. Still enjoying it. They're good kids, they're all desperate to learn. Adair the other day. And Shane looks like he's been playing for years.
Tim Murtagh is the Man of the Series.

Masakadza: We haven't played our best cricket, credit to Ireland. They showed us up and put us under the pump. We need to make better decisions under pressure. That's what Ireland have done, every time they're on top, they haven't let us come back.

5:58pm Handshakes as Ireland seal the series with a six-wicket win. They have Zimbabwe nothing today. A relentless attack with the new ball, aided by some irresponsible shots from Zimbabwe's top order, meant the visitors had no chance to ever think of a reasonable acceleration. This meant a total under 190, right in the comfort zone, and all of Ireland's batsmen barring Balbirnie got their little contributions in to seal the victory.

commentTextItems.html: inside edge past leg stump as he gets forward and has a jab at this length ball outside off. Rolls feebly to fine leg's right and they take a second

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza b Getkate 23 (46b 3x4 0x6) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: bowled him! Gap between bat and pad as Masakadza looks to drive on the up against a length ball outside off. It's past his inside edge and hits the top of the stumps

headshotImage.caption: Shane Getkate, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Shane Getkate, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalText.commentary: Sikandar Raza lbw b Getkate 6 (4b 1x4 0x6) SR: 150

dismissalComment.html: given lbw! Was just praising how he's been shuffling to open up the leg side, but it's exactly that which is his downfall. A length ball at off, with slant back into the stumps. He shuffles and looks to flick, but he's missed it altogether and is right in front of the stumps. They usually get the Raza rescue, Zimbabwe, but there won't be one today

headshotImage.caption: Mark Adair player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mark Adair player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Solomon Mire b Adair 14 (27b 1x4 0x6) SR: 51.85

dismissalComment.html: bowled him! Looks like an inside edge. Mire had started to look very solid and organized, but he's looked for an expansive drive without moving his front foot. Massive gap between bat and pad. Ball hits the outside of leg stump

headshotImage.caption: Boyd Rankin player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Boyd Rankin player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Lorcan Tucker, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Lorcan Tucker, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalText.commentary: Richmond Mutumbami c †Tucker b Rankin 28 (33b 4x4 0x6) SR: 84.84

dismissalComment.html: and gone! Short of length outside off, Mutumbami pushes at it, gets an outside edge and Tucker takes a fine catch to his right

headshotImage.caption: Mark Adair player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mark Adair player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.longCaption: Mark Adair player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams run out (Adair) 67 (103b 6x4 0x6) SR: 65.04

dismissalComment.html: an unfortunate run-out at the non-striker's end. Was a short ball outside off, Jarvis smashes it straight back at the bowler who fails to catch it but the deflection breaks the stumps at the bowler's end and Williams wasn't quick enough to get back, departs for 67

headshotImage.longCaption: Tyrone Kane player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kyle Jarvis c sub (TE Kane) b Rankin 28 (33b 3x4 1x6) SR: 84.84

dismissalComment.html: short of length around off, Jarvis is cramped for the room as he look to hit through the off side, an easy catch for the substitute fielder at point

headshotImage.caption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Tendai Chatara b Murtagh 1 (6b 0x4 0x6) SR: 16.66

dismissalComment.html: bowled 'im! So the drop doesn't prove expensive as Murtagh yorks Chatara for his third wicket of the game

dismissalText.commentary: Paul Stirling c †Taylor b Chatara 32 (44b 5x4 0x6) SR: 72.72

dismissalComment.html: got him! Stirling won't become the second ODI batsman to get seven 50-plus scores in a row. Short of a length outside off, looks to cut but that gets big on him late and he can only edge it behind

headshotImage.longCaption: James McCollum player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Ryan Burl player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ryan Burl player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: James McCollum c Burl b Mire 54 (69b 6x4 1x6) SR: 78.26

dismissalComment.html: fuller outside off, looks to carve it through the off side but ends up slicing it towards point where Burl takes a good low catch

dismissalText.commentary: Andy Balbirnie c Mutumbami b Williams 5 (9b 1x4 0x6) SR: 55.55

dismissalComment.html: taken at mid-on. Balbirnie is late on the sweep and manages only a top edge out to the fielder. Length at off stump, pushed flat and he wants to sweep but is in terrible shape to pull it off

headshotImage.caption: Ryan Burl player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ryan Burl player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: William Porterfield b Burl 49 (69b 7x4 0x6) SR: 71.01

dismissalComment.html: bowled him! Porterfield falls short of a fifty. Burl rewarded for his eight nicely landed legbreaks that built the pressure. Rips this in from a length outside off as Porterfield backs away to try and punch through cover. Past the inside edge and into middle and off

dismissalText.commentary: Kevin O'Brien not out 35 (44b 4x4 0x6) SR: 79.54
